The paper deals with image classification using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of saliency maps and multi-channel CNN architecture also suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves improving performance over existing approaches, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
